HEADWORD: Rotator
<hw>Ro*ta"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>that which gives a rotary or rolling
motion, as a muscle which partially rotates or turns some part on its
axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>A revolving reverberatory
furnace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rotatoria</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
